1
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:51,972
LINK

2
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:54,352
EXCHANGING LETTERS WITH FRIENDS
MAILBOX OF LOVE

3
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,933
GRADE 3, CLASS 7, FRIENDSHIP MAILBOX

4
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:02,848
I doubt there are any for you.

5
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,565
-I'm so envious.
-You got so many letters.

6
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:12,163
-How many did you get?
-By the way…

7
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,488
How many? Six? Twelve?

8
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,084
-I got 13.
-Wow.

9
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,789
-Hey, Eun Gyehoon!
-You got 12?

10
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:19,949
Are you happy
that you got so many letters?

11
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:22,038
<i>-Perhaps I am</i>
-You can't get me!

12
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:23,705
<i>dreaming.</i>

13
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:26,210
<i>It's a little embarrassing, but maybe</i>

14
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:28,418
<i>it's a happy dream.</i>

15
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:44,021
<i>No way.</i>

16
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:58,408
MISSING CHILD
EUN GYEYOUNG, AGE 10

17
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,253
<i>It was probably the day</i>

18
00:02:08,753 --> 00:02:10,843
<i>that I got the most letters in my life.</i>

19
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:13,677
<i>"Cheer up."</i>

20
00:02:13,758 --> 00:02:14,928
<i>"I'll pray for you."</i>

21
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,589
<i>"Don't lose hope."</i>

22
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,425
<i>On that day, all those consoling words</i>

23
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:21,724
<i>made me feel nauseous,</i>

24
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:26,692
<i>and I ended up
only remembering two of the letters.</i>

25
00:02:27,897 --> 00:02:29,017
<i>One of them was…</i>

26
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:32,277
<i>To my brother Eun Gyehoon
from Eun Gyeyoung.</i>

27
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:37,028
<i>I know you told on Mom
that I skipped my piano lesson.</i>

28
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:39,985
<i>I'm very angry, but I'll forgive you.</i>

29
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:42,536
<i>However, there are a few conditions.</i>

30
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:45,749
<i>First. Don't ever tell on me again.</i>

31
00:02:46,457 --> 00:02:50,707
<i>Second. If I get scolded by Mom and Dad,
take my side no matter what.</i>

32
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:52,262
<i>Third.</i>

33
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:55,428
<i>The letter that Gyeyoung wrote me
before she disappeared.</i>

34
00:02:56,426 --> 00:02:58,546
<i>And another letter.</i>

35
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:01,257
<i>I have something to confess.</i>

36
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:05,185
<i>You really have to keep this a secret.</i>

37
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:07,435
<i>The day Gyeyoung disappeared…</i>

38
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:09,938
<i>Actually…</i>

39
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:15,275
<i>Someone's… confession.</i>

40
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:18,661
CONFESSION

41
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:32,961
Why did I dream that?

42
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,135
<i>The body…</i>

43
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,100
<i>disappeared.</i>

44
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:15,229
Did you find what you were looking for?

45
00:05:31,539 --> 00:05:35,129
<i>Did this guy… move it?</i>

46
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:36,877
No.

47
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,507
What really happened?

48
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:44,508
Did you hear what I said?

49
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:49,019
Well, nothing happened. The thing is that…

50
00:05:50,224 --> 00:05:52,354
I was walking by,
and your store door was opened.

51
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:54,895
So I came inside
to check up on it, but it's fine

52
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:56,899
and now that you're here too,
I'll get going--

53
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:58,651
You want me to believe that lie?

54
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,620
Yes.

55
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,580
Ms. Noh.

56
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:27,352
Maybe I'm on your side.

57
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,030
Seriously, what happened?

58
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:11,240
EPISODE 3

59
00:08:24,086 --> 00:08:25,706
Is your husband competing in the Olympics?

60
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:28,220
Why does he exercise so hard?

61
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:32,259
I have no idea. Perhaps he's having
a midlife crisis. He's odd these days.

62
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:34,055
It's better than being weak and frail.

63
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:38,890
Stop wasting time looking at him,
and look over there.

64
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:51,702
My goodness.

65
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:53,451
You're sweating so much.

66
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,243
-Would you like some water?
-No thank you.

67
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,576
-Some <i>misu</i> shake?
-No.

68
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:57,581
-Juice?
-Bread?

69
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,962
-No thank you.
-If you need anything living here…

70
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,919
-I'm fine.
-There's a free aerobics class at night.

71
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:03,879
-I'm not going.
-Here you go.

72
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,250
-Thank you,
-Oh come on.

73
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,666
but it's okay. See you later.

74
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,009
-Wait… Young man!
-Juice…

75
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,261
Young man, just drink one cup!

76
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:14,182
He's the rudest of all, for sure.

77
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,541
<i>Don't worry about your mom at all.</i>

78
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:42,416
She said the flowers are beautiful
that butterflies will fly over.

79
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:44,878
She's still young at heart.

80
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,212
<i>Thank you, Aunt.</i>

81
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:48,214
Thanks to you,
I don't have to worry about being here.

82
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:52,716
Your mom throws a fuss at you because
she's sick, not because she hates you.

83
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,090
<i>Her mind is ill. You know that, right?</i>

84
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:56,507
Yes, I do. Of course.

85
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:59,523
Okay. Take care.

86
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:01,388
Bye.

87
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,018
This is your place?

88
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:09,646
Completely moving out?

89
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:12,109
I'll go back and forth from my mom's.

90
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:17,030
It's also an employee lounge.
Feel free to use it.

91
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:20,787
You want me to rest here?

92
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:22,750
That's like saying,

93
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:26,000
"Skip class and have fun
in the teachers' office."

94
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,083
Be quiet.

95
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:30,003
How can you…

96
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:34,126
Why is he making me rest here?

97
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:37,796
I don't want to…

98
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:41,599
Oh, check out this view.

99
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:45,015
Gyehoon, you can see the entire alley.

100
00:10:47,772 --> 00:10:50,362
Wake up!
Aren't you going to eat breakfast?

101
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:52,488
Not eating.

102
00:10:52,568 --> 00:10:55,528
I set up the table a long time ago.
You're still sleeping? Hey!

103
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:59,583
I didn't get any sleep last night
and just fell asleep.

104
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:02,366
Why does she keep locking the door?

105
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:05,367
The rice and soup are
getting cold, you brat!

106
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:06,996
I don't feel like eating!

107
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,593
Sleep more after eating. Eat!

108
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,546
-Eat!
-Jeez.

109
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:16,183
I told you that the soup is getting cold!

110
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:18,007
I'm going to knock the door down!

111
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:21,764
Hey, get up. I said, get up!

112
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:24,427
Get up! Hey!

113
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,687
Get up and come out
while I'm still being nice.

114
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,061
-Seriously, you brat.
-Okay.

115
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:32,476
-I'm up. I said, I'm up!
-Hey!

116
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:37,153
Gosh, seriously. That darn food!

117
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:45,958
Gyehoon, are you really her stalker?

118
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:49,924
-No.
-Yes, you are.

119
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:55,338
No, I am not.
I've never opened this window before,

120
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,553
and I had no idea
who lived in front of me.

121
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,433
-So it's a coincidence?
-Of course.

122
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:03,350
Who checks who the neighbors are
before renting a place? Of course, I--

123
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:06,141
Some people do check
before they rent a place.

124
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:08,386
Who?

125
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:09,597
Stalkers.

126
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:13,108
He shouldn't be doing this.

127
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:16,821
Hey.

128
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:25,869
You said the rice was ready
a long time ago.

129
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:27,663
You said the soup is all cold now!

130
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:30,247
<i>Delicious steamed rice is now ready.</i>

131
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,212
<i>-Please stir it well.</i>
-It says it's ready now.

132
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:50,099
<i>Since that day…</i>

133
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:09,294
<i>my entire family had developed trauma.</i>

134
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,228
I'll leave the package
in front of your door.

135
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:39,026
Why is he delivering
so early in the morning?

136
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:40,993
He's so diligent. How nice.

137
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:44,911
That's true. It's admirable
that he's working hard.

138
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:46,657
<i>We've also become afraid</i>

139
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:49,452
<i>of being arrested at any moment.</i>

140
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:53,535
I can't keep living like this anymore.

141
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:55,794
We have to put an end to this right away.

142
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:58,667
I'll get it back from that sly chef--

143
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,714
That's not necessary.
It's not there anyway.

144
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,804
What's not there?

145
00:14:04,134 --> 00:14:05,144
The refrigerator?

146
00:14:07,137 --> 00:14:09,307
No. That guy…

147
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:12,018
disappeared.

148
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:15,228
What?

149
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:17,436
The refrigerator is empty.

150
00:14:19,483 --> 00:14:21,033
How would you know that?

151
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,196
Because I opened it.

152
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:25,279
When? Tell us. How?

153
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:29,537
I snuck in last night and opened it--

154
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:35,076
-Mom.
-How is that you have no fear?

155
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:38,502
You snuck in there in the middle
of the night? On top of it, by yourself?

156
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:41,126
But nothing happened. Why did you hit me?

157
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:43,223
What nonsense! Should I just kill you?

158
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:45,179
Just kill me then.
I'm an eyesore to you anyway.

159
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:47,049
Is that right? Fine. Let's do that. Great.

160
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:50,176
Stop it. Grandma!

161
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,934
How can you have an appetite after that?

162
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:53,056
You told me to eat, Mom.

163
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:55,482
And I can always eat whenever
and under any circumstance.

164
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,901
-That's just how I am. I can't help it.
-Are you proud of it?

165
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,440
No, I'm not. It's just how I am.

166
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:00,983
Shameless. Who does she take after?

167
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,356
Who else, but you?

168
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:03,613
Seriously, you brat!

169
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:07,698
Gosh, be quiet. That's enough.

170
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:11,414
You, you, and me.
Even if we combined all our intelligence,

171
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:14,713
it still isn't as good as one person's.
So what should we do then?

172
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,368
Should we continue to fight like this
or combine our strengths?

173
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:20,133
Answer me!

174
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:24,628
-Combine our strengths.
-Combine…

175
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:27,006
Come and eat now.

176
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:38,152
So we must think carefully

177
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:41,114
step by step.

178
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,067
The body disappeared…

179
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:46,821
The body disappeared?

180
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:53,696
Unless we're all having the same dream,
it must be…

181
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:58,535
-Jinhoo. Taste this.
-Yes?

182
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:01,418
-It's hot.
<i>-Either that guy moved it</i>

183
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:05,258
<i>or someone else did.</i>

184
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:07,174
-Good.
-Okay.

185
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:17,845
Gyehoon, I think I have superpowers now.

186
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:19,895
I can feel things like you.

187
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:23,153
Ever since we came to this neighborhood,
something changed.

188
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:26,362
How should I describe it? It feels like
the dead cells in my body are awake.

189
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:39,922
<i>I feel like people keep watching us.</i>

190
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:44,999
<i>It's like we're trapped inside of a jail
with constant surveillance.</i>

191
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:50,800
<i>It's like </i>The Truman Show.

192
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,006
Gosh.

193
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:05,017
Even now, they're all looking at us.

194
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:07,858
It's because
we're walking around like this.

195
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:14,742
Jeez, get off of me.

196
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,333
But this neighborhood is scary.

197
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:24,292
-By the way, I have a question for you.
-Don't ask.

198
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:27,963
Is that Wi-Fi girl from the stew place

199
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:30,667
really your long-lost sister?

200
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,973
Is that really the case?
She's your sister?

201
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:39,728
I don't think she is.

202
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:41,018
But she could be.

203
00:17:43,687 --> 00:17:45,307
There is always a chance.

204
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,944
But if…

205
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,565
she isn't Gyeyoung…

206
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:02,214
how did I sense all those feelings?

207
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,629
Why don't you confirm it?

208
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:07,920
You can just ask her directly
or go run some tests.

209
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:12,545
-I'm afraid.
-That she might not be your sister?

210
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,301
That she might be your sister?

211
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:17,759
Or both?

212
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:20,677
Perhaps.

213
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,267
Does she look a bit like her?

214
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:27,225
What did your sister look like?

215
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:34,735
<i>When we were kids, we made fun
of each other saying the other was ugly.</i>

216
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:37,159
<i>But objectively speaking, she was pretty.</i>

217
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,536
More than anything, she was smart.

218
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:43,908
Although she was very timid,
she was always cheerful.

219
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:48,634
Our relatives and elders
in the neighborhood

220
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:51,300
said she looked so neat and elegant
even though she's a kid--

221
00:18:59,054 --> 00:18:59,894
What?

222
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:04,098
Why are you staring at me?

223
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,188
I'm not sure.

224
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:10,477
MOTHER'S TASTE
CHOONOK STEW

225
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:54,572
Darn it.

226
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:57,991
Those women are suspicious indeed.

227
00:19:58,071 --> 00:19:59,281
Are they?

228
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:02,622
Oh, right. Ma'am.

229
00:20:02,951 --> 00:20:04,661
Do they visit our patrol unit for fun?

230
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,245
The entire family came by
to turn themselves in.

231
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:09,541
But in the end,
they said they just stopped by.

232
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,417
-Does that make sense to you?
-Is that the case?

233
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,295
-Ma'am.
-Make sure you show me respect.

234
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:18,632
Yes, ma'am.

235
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:20,723
<i>Jihwa Apartment, Jihwa 3-ro.</i>

236
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:22,222
<i>A woman's scream next door.</i>

237
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:24,224
"A woman's scream next door.
Domestic violence."

238
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:25,973
<i>-Are you available?</i>
-It's near.

239
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,018
Turn right next.

240
00:20:27,976 --> 00:20:30,646
This is patrol 11.
Report number 852. We'll go.

241
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:35,114
Ma'am!

242
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:37,073
Is anyone inside?

243
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,530
Ma'am!

244
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,493
I said, you're mistaken.

245
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:44,123
We received a report, so we must check.

246
00:20:47,287 --> 00:20:49,247
How many times do I have to tell you?

247
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:50,961
Nothing happened. I'm home alone.

248
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:55,299
If you need our help discreetly,

249
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:57,299
can you nod gently?

250
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,588
No, I don't. Please leave.

251
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:04,303
Please go on.

252
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,479
Excuse us. We're going to check.

253
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,439
Nothing is going on!

254
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:16,399
-Who are you guys?
-We're the police.

255
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:19,573
We came to check after receiving a call.
We ask for your cooperation.

256
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:22,243
-Did you call them?
-No, I didn't.

257
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,865
I guess something did happen.

258
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:30,082
Come on, don't do that.

259
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:33,625
I said, nothing is going on.
Please leave now.

260
00:21:35,043 --> 00:21:36,463
Officer Ji, you stay out of it.

261
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:37,957
Look, sir.

262
00:21:38,714 --> 00:21:40,264
Look, police lady.

263
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,510
I'm not a "police lady."
Please call me officer.

264
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:43,682
I think

265
00:21:44,469 --> 00:21:46,809
there has been a misunderstanding.

266
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:51,978
Any unnecessary physical contact
should be done to me.

267
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:03,356
What are you doing?
Why don't you dress properly, rookie?

268
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:06,067
I'm sorry, ma'am. It's a habit
not to put on clothes after showering.

269
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,368
I'm aware of that habit.

270
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,195
-Can you move out of my way?
-Sure.

271
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:18,422
For cases like earlier,

272
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:20,804
is there anything else we can do?

273
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:22,971
Domestic violence
can't be punished over objection,

274
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:25,050
so if the victim doesn't want
to punish the offender,

275
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,385
there is nothing we can do.

276
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:29,508
Why isn't she reporting him?

277
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:30,888
She doesn't trust the law.

278
00:22:33,101 --> 00:22:35,811
By the way, we're off duty tomorrow.
Do you have plans, ma'am?

279
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:37,106
I don't have any plans,

280
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:40,319
but my credo is
not to spend time with subordinates.

281
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:42,362
So no thanks
to eating or going out for drinks.

282
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:45,284
-I guess you seek people with power.
-Yes, very, extremely so.

283
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:47,027
I'm a very ambitious woman.

284
00:22:47,657 --> 00:22:48,827
I'm heading out now.

285
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:52,698
Bye, ma'am.

286
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:55,578
MOTHER'S TASTE
CHOONOK STEW

287
00:23:02,297 --> 00:23:03,877
You came to spy on us again?

288
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:07,175
No, I just came to eat.
I missed a home-cooked meal.

289
00:23:07,803 --> 00:23:09,143
Wow, it looks delicious.

290
00:23:14,434 --> 00:23:15,734
What? It doesn't taste good?

291
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:18,151
It does. It's good.

292
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:20,566
By the way, where is your daughter?

293
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:22,569
Why? So you can harass her again?

294
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:24,691
No, I want to get to know her.

295
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:28,068
There aren't many people my age
around here, so it's nice to see her.

296
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:33,294
And I'm supposed to believe pigs can fly?

297
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:48,427
Ma'am, I have a question for you.

298
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:49,720
Yes, go ahead.

299
00:23:53,473 --> 00:23:55,393
Have you seen him before?

300
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:57,693
Let's see.

301
00:23:58,437 --> 00:24:00,397
He does look a little familiar.
Right, Mom?

302
00:24:00,522 --> 00:24:01,572
Yes, he does.

303
00:24:02,983 --> 00:24:05,403
But… maybe not.

304
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:06,954
You're right.

305
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:09,783
Who is he? Does he owe you money?

306
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,239
He's my younger brother.

307
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:15,538
Did he run away from home or something?

308
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:17,329
I suddenly lost touch with him.

309
00:24:18,081 --> 00:24:20,541
I'm sorry we couldn't be of much help.

310
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:23,590
We have so many customers that come and go

311
00:24:23,670 --> 00:24:25,800
that we can't remember everyone.

312
00:24:25,881 --> 00:24:28,051
It doesn't look like
you have that many customers.

313
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,223
Pardon?

314
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:31,640
How much is the bill?

315
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,350
Sure, yes. It's 24,000 won.

316
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:35,641
-Insert your credit card.
-Okay.

317
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:39,135
Did you enjoy the food?

318
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:41,937
I can't say it was good
even if I wanted to be polite.

319
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:45,864
It tasted like you didn't use any MSG.

320
00:24:45,942 --> 00:24:49,112
That's right. I cook the food
as if I'm feeding my own child.

321
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:52,486
If that's the case,
you should put in a little more effort.

322
00:24:52,574 --> 00:24:53,954
It was a little problematic.

323
00:24:54,534 --> 00:24:58,254
The stir-fried spicy pork had
the smell of freezer burn,

324
00:24:58,830 --> 00:25:03,210
and you generously put all sorts of herbs
in the boiled pork wraps for good health.

325
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:05,052
You shouldn't have.

326
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:07,587
I'd rather take herbal medicine
if that was the case.

327
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:10,343
And how did you steam
the mung bean sprouts?

328
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:12,224
Please take your card.

329
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:13,722
Please throw away the receipt.

330
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:16,143
You just need to quickly
blanch the sprouts in boiling water.

331
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:17,063
Sure, sure.

332
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:20,809
-Just quickly. Not too long.
-Okay, go on.

333
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:43,629
LEE JINGEUN

334
00:25:48,129 --> 00:25:49,339
Hello?

335
00:25:50,006 --> 00:25:50,836
<i>Hello--</i>

336
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,850
<i>The phone is switched off.</i>

337
00:25:57,931 --> 00:25:58,971
<i>Transferring to voicemail--</i>

338
00:26:22,289 --> 00:26:23,119
Oh, my.

339
00:26:23,665 --> 00:26:25,205
-I'm sorry.
-Are you all right?

340
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,502
You're so kind.

341
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:28,085
Don't mention it.

342
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:36,217
You're so pretty.

343
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,260
You're totally my type.

344
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:46,439
I'm sorry. I went too far
when we just met, right? I'm sorry.

345
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:47,521
It's okay.

346
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:50,779
-Bye then.
-Bye.

347
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:54,026
Bye.

348
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:07,132
She's right. I'm so pretty.

349
00:27:08,209 --> 00:27:09,499
So pretty…

350
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:10,796
MOTHER'S TASTE
CHOONOK STEW

351
00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:30,978
Jeez, the police are everywhere.

352
00:27:36,571 --> 00:27:38,531
<i>Those women are suspicious indeed.</i>

353
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:42,040
Hello.

354
00:27:43,036 --> 00:27:44,156
You know who I am, right?

355
00:27:44,245 --> 00:27:45,575
You came to the patrol unit a lot.

356
00:27:46,247 --> 00:27:47,787
We saw each other so often.

357
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:49,205
Right?

358
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:51,381
I know you can hear everything.

359
00:27:53,004 --> 00:27:55,474
Pardon me.
I just need to talk to you briefly…

360
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:03,137
Why is she always anxious? It's annoying.

361
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:12,440
<i>If you were attacked</i>

362
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,744
by someone like I was,

363
00:28:15,819 --> 00:28:17,649
what would you do?

364
00:28:17,737 --> 00:28:20,487
If this happened to my younger sister,

365
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:23,124
<i>that attacker would've died by my hand.</i>

366
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:30,380
Gosh, why are you doing this to me?

367
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:34,248
I'm just checking to see if you're okay
since you're making me worry.

368
00:28:34,337 --> 00:28:36,167
Am I? Why?

369
00:28:36,256 --> 00:28:39,626
It's not common for the entire family
to visit the patrol unit.

370
00:28:39,843 --> 00:28:43,143
Oh, my! I thought that was quite common.

371
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:46,055
I believe the patrol unit is
like a guest lounge,

372
00:28:46,141 --> 00:28:47,981
a very welcoming place for the citizens--

373
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:50,809
I can tell from your eyes
that you're lying.

374
00:28:51,479 --> 00:28:52,899
Are you interrogating me?

375
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:55,151
No, I'm just greeting you.

376
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:57,493
I see. That was enough of a greeting.
See you later.

377
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:58,779
Wait a minute.

378
00:28:58,862 --> 00:29:02,162
-I apologize if I offended you or--
-Are you all right?

379
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:07,245
-Is he the one?
-Pardon?

380
00:29:08,121 --> 00:29:09,961
-Who the heck are you?
-Is he the one?

381
00:29:10,039 --> 00:29:11,669
Can't you hear me? Who the heck are you?

382
00:29:11,791 --> 00:29:13,171
What do you think you're doing?

383
00:29:13,251 --> 00:29:15,591
What did I do? Do you even know who I am?

384
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:18,340
-It's not what you think.
-You're afraid of him. You're scaring her!

385
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,263
No, it's not like that!

386
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:23,601
He's a policeman.
We were just saying hello.

387
00:29:26,389 --> 00:29:29,019
He misunderstands
and doubts people easily.

388
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:30,850
Apologize to the police officer now.

389
00:29:32,061 --> 00:29:33,811
-But I--
-Do it now.

390
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:36,230
I apologize too. I'm sorry.

391
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:40,486
This was clearly assault.

392
00:29:46,367 --> 00:29:48,997
I misunderstood the situation
since you were being suspicious,

393
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:51,582
but I apologize.

394
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:55,628
It's not common to feel upset
after receiving an apology.

395
00:29:57,086 --> 00:29:58,246
My name is Eun Gyehoon.

396
00:30:00,381 --> 00:30:01,761
Eun Gyehoon, I see.

397
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:05,345
No thanks.

398
00:30:05,929 --> 00:30:07,349
Apology not accepted.

399
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:11,015
-See you around again.
-Bye.

400
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:20,527
Well, I'll get going too.

401
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:23,567
Hey.

402
00:30:26,741 --> 00:30:28,911
What's wrong with you?
Why do you meddle in my affairs?

403
00:30:30,745 --> 00:30:32,615
You really don't know?
I was trying to help--

404
00:30:32,705 --> 00:30:35,165
After helping, did you think
that I'd be impressed

405
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:37,960
and fall for you like in a soap opera?

406
00:30:38,044 --> 00:30:40,344
-That's not the case.
-What a relief.

407
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:42,299
What did you say?

408
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:44,433
Keep your word.

409
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:46,339
Don't let your heart flutter
and fall for me

410
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:47,637
or like me like in soaps.

411
00:30:49,013 --> 00:30:51,393
Jeez, why would I like you?

412
00:30:51,474 --> 00:30:52,644
<i>I like you.</i>

413
00:30:52,725 --> 00:30:54,765
Look here! Look at me!

414
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:57,944
I like you.

415
00:31:00,108 --> 00:31:02,438
I did like you. I did, but…

416
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:06,487
Did you just dump me saying I shouldn't
like you anymore? You're so heartless.

417
00:31:06,573 --> 00:31:07,783
<i>What am I saying?</i>

418
00:31:10,952 --> 00:31:12,872
I knew you were lying.

419
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:15,075
I meant it,

420
00:31:15,164 --> 00:31:18,504
but since you're rejecting me like this,
I'll let you go. I'll stop liking you.

421
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:21,455
Make sure you keep your word.
Even if going forward, I…

422
00:31:24,799 --> 00:31:26,719
<i>Even if I mistake you for my sister and…</i>

423
00:31:27,051 --> 00:31:30,261
…treat you well, don't like me. Ever.

424
00:31:31,431 --> 00:31:33,471
-Okay, got it.
-Promise.

425
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:35,388
I promise. Satisfied?

426
00:31:36,853 --> 00:31:38,693
Yes. See you later then.

427
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:52,494
MOTHER'S TASTE
CHOONOK STEW

428
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,461
I can't live being so anxious like this.

429
00:32:06,466 --> 00:32:08,636
She didn't really know anything.

430
00:32:08,843 --> 00:32:11,183
But if the police keep coming here
and we talk to them,

431
00:32:11,262 --> 00:32:13,182
we'll get nervous
and end up making a mistake.

432
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:14,524
That's true.

433
00:32:17,101 --> 00:32:18,731
Should we send her abroad?

434
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:22,357
Or should all three of us go?

435
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,030
I'll be fine with that,
but how will you argue abroad?

436
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:26,606
You won't be able to communicate.

437
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,867
Why is life so difficult?

438
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:33,662
Darn it.

439
00:32:33,743 --> 00:32:35,373
ADMINISTRATION LITIGATION ACT

440
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:39,293
LEE JINGEUN'S WHEREABOUTS, WHERE?
I'M LOSING MY MIND!

441
00:32:50,677 --> 00:32:52,297
LOOK FOR A PART-TIME JOB EASILY

442
00:32:52,387 --> 00:32:54,217
JIHWA-GU, JIHWA-DONG

443
00:33:36,472 --> 00:33:38,982
<i>The body disappeared?</i>

444
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:41,484
<i>Either that guy moved it</i>

445
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:44,606
or someone else did.

446
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:46,519
Or if not,

447
00:33:46,607 --> 00:33:49,357
that body walked out alive.

448
00:35:57,446 --> 00:35:59,116
MOTHER'S TASTE
CHOONOK STEW

449
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,884
I couldn't sleep,
so I snuck out a bottle of soju.

450
00:36:17,383 --> 00:36:18,893
I couldn't sleep either.

451
00:36:20,970 --> 00:36:21,970
Well…

452
00:36:28,227 --> 00:36:29,347
Do you…

453
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:33,901
need a snack to go with it?

454
00:37:21,822 --> 00:37:22,662
I…

455
00:37:23,324 --> 00:37:24,834
Just in case, let me make it clear.

456
00:37:25,785 --> 00:37:27,445
Don't fall for me because I cook for you--

457
00:37:27,536 --> 00:37:29,746
I won't fall for you or like you. Okay?

458
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:31,745
Okay.

459
00:37:47,765 --> 00:37:51,055
The phlorotannins found in seaweed
are good for insomnia.

460
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:53,854
Oh, I see. Thank you for the food.

461
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:43,783
That…

462
00:39:17,730 --> 00:39:18,560
Gosh, it's cold.

463
00:39:30,659 --> 00:39:31,789
No need to be formal.

464
00:39:54,642 --> 00:39:56,352
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

465
00:40:01,315 --> 00:40:03,355
-Is it good?
-It's so soft.

466
00:40:03,484 --> 00:40:05,654
-Pardon?
-I said, it's so soft.

467
00:40:22,628 --> 00:40:24,508
I'm really curious.

468
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:27,008
Why are you doing all this for me?

469
00:40:28,676 --> 00:40:30,966
I'm testing the menu items
that I'm preparing,

470
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:34,101
and I also want
to get a good night's sleep.

471
00:40:35,724 --> 00:40:38,604
Because someone has trouble sleeping,
I can't sleep either.

472
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,976
-So I'm trying to help them.
-Pardon?

473
00:40:41,564 --> 00:40:42,524
You wouldn't understand.

474
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:47,534
I thought about it, but the fact

475
00:40:47,611 --> 00:40:50,281
that you're cooking
such heartfelt dishes for me--

476
00:40:50,364 --> 00:40:52,914
You promised.
Even if I treat you so well--

477
00:40:52,992 --> 00:40:54,622
I won't fall for you or like you. But--

478
00:40:55,202 --> 00:40:56,122
But what?

479
00:40:56,203 --> 00:40:58,463
But it seems strange from my perspective.

480
00:41:02,418 --> 00:41:03,838
Then how about this reason?

481
00:41:05,671 --> 00:41:07,131
It just came to my mind.

482
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:08,764
Jeez, that's ridiculous.

483
00:41:11,051 --> 00:41:12,221
A long time ago,

484
00:41:12,928 --> 00:41:15,388
I owed a friend five packs of <i>ramyeon.</i>

485
00:41:16,682 --> 00:41:20,022
<i>I ended up
only remembering two of the letters.</i>

486
00:41:20,269 --> 00:41:21,189
<i>Third.</i>

487
00:41:21,270 --> 00:41:23,980
<i>Cook</i> ramyeon <i>for me
when I'm hungry five times.</i>

488
00:41:24,231 --> 00:41:27,031
<i>Fourth.
Bring an umbrella when it's raining.</i>

489
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:28,650
<i>Promise me, okay?</i>

490
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:33,737
<i>Cook</i> ramyeon <i>for her
when she's hungry five times.</i>

491
00:41:35,701 --> 00:41:36,791
But…

492
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:40,786
now I'll never be able to do it for her,

493
00:41:42,124 --> 00:41:44,384
and perhaps I'm doing it for you instead.

494
00:41:50,466 --> 00:41:51,796
I see.

495
00:41:53,969 --> 00:41:57,719
That's why we shouldn't
take people for granted.

496
00:42:03,062 --> 00:42:04,192
You're right.

497
00:42:25,501 --> 00:42:28,961
-Grandma.
-My goodness. Studying is tough, isn't it?

498
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:30,837
Yes, it is.

499
00:42:31,465 --> 00:42:35,465
The chef of that restaurant over there

500
00:42:36,178 --> 00:42:38,428
doesn't seem like a bad person.

501
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:40,934
He wouldn't move a body
out of the refrigerator.

502
00:42:41,016 --> 00:42:43,846
What happened to you wasn't because
you were a bad person either.

503
00:42:45,187 --> 00:42:46,107
That's true.

504
00:42:47,106 --> 00:42:48,896
-I'll be back.
-Okay.

505
